						               													<description>La sfida del coding is a game to take the first steps in programming, using only cardboard components.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Initially, the game proposes 24 puzzles to solve in which players have to move their robot to the destination using the directional cards: the puzzles are of increasing difficulty and present, by hand, additional elements such as walls and special cards.&amp;#10; The game contains 4 plastic robots, 4 modular boards, 24 tiles and 132 cards to challenge the others in races that are always different and full of twists.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each player has 7 cards in his hand and he secretly plays 3, simultaneously with the opponents: players turn one card at a time and make their robots perform the corresponding action.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;There are 3 progressive game modes: in the basic version, only directional cards are used, in the middle version there are also shots and in the advanced one there are special cards such as routines, shields and magnets.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The tiles can be arranged as desired on the boards to give life to different paths.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The particular thing of the advanced version is that, in addition to creating paths as desired, players can also customize the decks, choosing the special cards to play with.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;-description from designer&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
